About BlackSquare

BlackSquare is the global digital experience leader in the alcohol beverage space. We provide direct to consumer turnkey marketing, operations, logistics, and distribution technology-enabled managed services, as well as ecommerce software as a service (SaaS) and data analytics. We are a relentlessly resourceful group of people. Everyone in the company has the freedom to work independently, to solve problems and to get things done for our clients. It’s that entrepreneurial attitude that underpins everything we do together.

The Role

The Data Analyst will be responsible for identifying, collecting, analyzing and presenting digital commerce related data for our clients. This position will be focussed on mining and linking data, creating dashboards, and reporting on key performance indicators to allow our clients to maximize the performance of their digital commerce sites. The role will also be a key liaison between business teams and technical teams in gathering requirements, translating requirements and participating in user acceptance testing to ensure requirements have been met.

Specifically, the Data Analyst will be responsible to:
Implement global eCommerce data solutions to provide information to clients and identify key factors impacting digital commerce performance;
Measure customer acquisition, cost of acquisition, and identify challenges and opportunities;
Create and automate reports and dashboards that link multiple data sources, ultimately measuring the end-to-end digital customer journey
Identify and report on key performance indicators of our digital commerce solutions, providing insights back to the product team that can be used to build best in class solutions
Work closely with the development team and business teams to gather requirements and to translate proposed solutions into functional specifications, implement them and maintain documentation for digital analysis projects;
Participate in implementation and continuous improvement of various data solutions;
Participate in user acceptance testing events to ensure business requirements have been met.

Requirements:
Minimum 3-5 years’ experience as a technical ecommerce data analyst or similar role;
Post secondary education in a relevant discipline (Business, Computer Science, Engineering, Math)
Excellent analytical reasoning, problem solving, time management, and organizational skills;
Proven experience in process, functional and system integration analysis; creating, analyzing, and validating detailed specifications;
Experience working with development teams;
Excellent documentation, business process, data analysis, and solution design skills;
Experience in translating business requirements into technical requirements needed to develop and implement a software solution;
QA and testing experience including creation of test plans and leading user acceptance testing;
Experience with software development and its life cycle (SDLC);
Current on innovations in technology and industry trends; up-to-date knowledge of current technology techniques and tools.
Experience with measurement and analysis tools like Google Analytics, Power BI, and Advertising platform measurement tools.

