What Will You Do?
The transport Process Engineering group is looking for a candidate to fulfill the role of Opto-electrical assembly Engineer/Scientist. The products we manufacture are part of virtually every type of telecom, enterprise, and data centre network. The processing expertise gained by our team over 20 years is progressing into the next-generation technologies. The successful candidate will be directly involved in process design cycle from conceptual design, a first build prototype in our lab, device characterization using both manual and automated equipment, to high volume production by one of our contract manufactures. The position resides in Ottawa Telecom Transport Business Unit, but frequent business travel to Asia is expected.
If you have a passion for learning and solving problems as well as an educational background that includes materials science, physics, engineering, programming or directly related disciplines; as well as hands-on experience in assembly processes and equipment setup; - this role could be just what you seek.
Responsibilities include but not limited to:
Design, develop and qualify different area of Mfg. Process including but not limited to automated epoxy application, automated machine vision application, soldering, packaging and pick-and-place processes;
Specify the design and lead the assembly of tools and jigs. To assist with developing improved tooling and tool support strategies for manufacturing;
Sustain processes with emphasis on statistical process control, maintain yields and improve yields to targets. Improve manufacturability and defect reduction for different process areas of the fab by working closely with various process engineers;
Contribute to FMEA and DOE in the product design phase for performance and reliability validation;
Contribute to the transfer of new products to manufacturing sites and subsequent cost reductions;
Working within a cleanroom environment with the prerequisite use of cleanroom clothing;
